{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/why","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"web-development-is-accessible\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#web-development-is-accessible\" aria-label=\"web development is accessible permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Web Development is accessible!</h2>\n<p>All you need is a browser and a text editor and you can start coding for the internet!</p>\n<p>I wanted to create this course because (I enjoy teaching and) I think Web Development is particularly approachable for coding. A lot of other branches of software Engineering involve lots of tooling (AKA setting up stuff to do the things), and or are platform specific (like you need an iPhone or a Mac to make iPhone apps kinda thing), etc.</p>\n<p>I'd argue that most people in this room have probably used the internet at least once in there lives, and probably have a browser, so I think it's familiar enough to get you going!</p>\n<p><strong>My goal is to get you started programming</strong>, and remember everyone gets stuck! All of this stuff was made up by someone else anyway, so it's not always intuitive, so don't be too hard on yourself.</p>\n<p>Please, please, please ask questions along the way!</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/hackabull2021-intro-to-web-dev/static/22979d89a2e989e28147f8d2d2799074/b4294/programmer.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"programmer\" title=\"programmer\" src=\"/hackabull2021-intro-to-web-dev/static/22979d89a2e989e28147f8d2d2799074/b4294/programmer.jpg\" srcset=\"/hackabull2021-intro-to-web-dev/static/22979d89a2e989e28147f8d2d2799074/e07e9/programmer.jpg 200w,\n/hackabull2021-intro-to-web-dev/static/22979d89a2e989e28147f8d2d2799074/066f9/programmer.jpg 400w,\n/hackabull2021-intro-to-web-dev/static/22979d89a2e989e28147f8d2d2799074/b4294/programmer.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<br>\n<p>Other Things you'll hopefully learn on the way: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Random tricks for coding on the web</li>\n<li>Keyboard shortcuts maybe?</li>\n<li>The dev tools.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"outline-for-this-course\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#outline-for-this-course\" aria-label=\"outline for this course permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Outline for this course</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Tools you need to start coding for the web</li>\n<li>A gentle overview of how the web works</li>\n<li>The big 3 programming languages used for the web: (HTML, CSS, Javascript)</li>\n<li>Let's code!!!</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/why","title":"Why this course?","order":"1B","section":"Introduction","description":"Motivation for this course"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3B","path":"/cascading-style-sheets","title":"Cascading Style Sheets (CSS)"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"4A","path":"/goodbye","title":"Goodbye Fam"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3A","path":"/hyper-text-markup-language","title":"HyperText Markup Language (HTML)"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"1A","path":"/intro","title":"Intro"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3C","path":"/javascript","title":"Javascript (JS)"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"2B","path":"/the-big-3","title":"The Big 3"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"1C","path":"/tools","title":"Tools"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"1B","path":"/why","title":"Why this course?"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"2A","path":"/the-world-wide-web","title":"The World Wide Web"}}}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["2959687377"]}